>
>i read from a book that slopes of any two non vertical 
>perpendicular lines is '-1' but what do they mean non 
>vertical lines.

Hi Vijay, 

'Non-something' just means not something.  So a non-vertical line is
any line that isn't vertical.  A vertical line is a line that goes
straight up and down, like the y-axis, or any line parallel to the
y-axis. 

- Doctor Ian, The Math Forum
  <http://mathforum.org/dr.math/>

